&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s degree or two-year college certificate in any technical, industrial, or applied science discipline also accepted&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General knowledge of hand tools and basic mechanical aptitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to use precision measurement devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read blueprints and engineering drawings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and follow written and verbal instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with blueprint reading and basic GD&amp;amp;T (Geometric Dimensioning &amp;amp; Tolerancing) concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be a U.S. Person (U.S. Citizen, Lawful Permanent Resident, Refugee, or Asylee) per ITAR/EAR export control regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
