&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Cost Accounting Manager is responsible for analyzing, tracking, and reporting manufacturing and operational costs to support informed business decision-making. This role partners closely with operations, supply chain, engineering, and finance leadership to maintain cost integrity, drive margin improvement, and ensure accurate inventory valuation across the organization. The ideal candidate combines strong technical accounting expertise with a collaborative approach, exceptional analytical skills, and a continuous improvement mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
