&lt;li&gt;Perform variance analysis (purchase price, labor efficiency, and overhead absorption) and communicate findings and recommendations to management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the accounting impact of manufacturing processes and provide guidance on operational decisions affecting financial reporting, inventory valuation, and cost accounting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement process improvements to enhance cost accuracy, reporting efficiency, and internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and reconcile inventory accounts, including raw materials, work-in-process (WIP), and finished goods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support month-end and year-end close processes, including journal entries, accruals, and cost of goods sold (COGS) reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze product profitability, cost trends, and operational efficiency metrics to support strategic decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering and operations teams on new product cost estimates, bill of materials (BOM) reviews, and cost reduction initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare cost reports, dashboards, and ad hoc financial analyses for senior leadership and executive stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the development of annual budgets and quarterly forecasts related to manufacturing and operational costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct periodic physical inventory counts and cycle counts; investigate and resolve discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with GAAP, internal controls, and company accounting policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal and external audits by providing cost data, analyses, and supporting documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
